item.mdl_comment:
The module for the Simplicité Training platform. This module objective is to offer an easy way to deploy a custom documentation. It's a *Category* / *Lesson* / *Translations* model with a few additions such as *tags* or *pages*. The training module not only gives the ability to manage content, but it also serves a Vue.js front end (see the external object *TrnFront*).
The front end is served on the root url of your instance. For further details on the site mapping, see system parameter *URI_MAPPING*. More info available on the front end default home page.

item.sys_desc:
Examples : 

Simple usecase
---------------------------

Editing through UI, using Simplicité indexing

```json
{
	"edition_type": "UI",
	"index_type": "simplicite"
}
```

Advanced usecase
---------------------------

Editing through Filesystem (possible git repo), using ElasticSearch indexing

```json
{
	"edition_type": "FILESYSTEM",
	"filesystem_contentdir": "/path/to/directory/to/sync/with",
	"index_type": "elasticsearch",
	"esi_config": {
		"instance": "https://elasticsearchinstance.mydomain.not",
		"index": "docs_myinstance",
		"public_credentials":"user:password"
	}
}
```

item.tsl_simplehelp:
The code is the unique identifier of the category, and usually a URL-friendly version of the title, because it impacts the URL of its child lessons.

Example: http://my-fake-url.com/lesson/category-code/lesson-code

Defines the ordering of the category within its parent category (or at the root if it is a root category)

It is advised to increment the order 10 by 10 in case you need to intercalate new categories in the future.
Toggle to hide or display the category in the front-end website

The code is the unique identifier of the lesson, and usually a URL-friendly version of the title, because it impacts the URL of the lesson.

Example: http://my-fake-url.com/lesson/category-code/lesson-code

Defines the ordering of the lesson within its parent category.

It is advised to increment the order 10 by 10 in case you need to intercalate new lessons in the future.
Toggle to hide or display the lesson in the front-end website

Changes the layout of the lesson in the front-end.

  • in linear mode, the layout is a simple page, and including media must be done manually in the content
  • in tutorial mode, the layout is a grid with the text in the left side, and the media (video & images) in the right side

1. Not familiar with Markdown syntax? Check this guide
  2. To include an image, upload it in the lesson images and inset it with this syntax: ![](image.jpg)
  3. To include the video, you must set the lesson in tutorial mode (not linear)
For the video to be displayed, the lesson must be in tutorial visualisation, not in linear visualisation.
Une catégorie publiée est visible sur le site.
